# GVAS Parsing

Full field layouts and property tables: [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md).

## Completion gate

Do not start item-tracking work until deserialization runs on `public/SBS00.sav` to EOF without desync. Run `pnpm test` after parser changes; add hex fixtures for new property paths.

## Desync debugging

- "Unsupported type" or absurd string length (e.g. `0xbf1ec20b`) → parser out of sync; verify the **previous** property consumed exactly `Size` bytes.
- Collection items: primitives omit Name/Type/Size headers; `StructProperty` items include headers (sometimes with an extra 1-byte separator in arrays).
- `ByteProperty`: use metadata `EnumName` — enum is a string; raw byte is a single number.
- Unknown game types (e.g. `SELostProperty`): skip value using header `Size` if structure is unknown.
- Trailing data after top-level `None` is valid — do not force PropertyTag parsing past EOF.

## Safety

Respect `BinaryReader` limits (max 1024 bytes per variable read). Reject corrupt length/count fields early.

